  "prompt": "Is Tufts University a good college (moreover, a good engineering college)?",
  "response": "Tufts University is generally considered a good college and is respected for its academic programs, including engineering. It is ranked among the top universities in the United States and is known for its strong liberal arts curriculum, diverse student body, and emphasis on research and interdisciplinary learning.\n\nSpecifically for engineering, Tufts' School of Engineering offers programs in various fields, including mechanical, electrical, civil, biomedical, and computer engineering. The university focuses on integrating engineering education with the liberal arts, which can provide students with a well-rounded education and prepare them for diverse career paths.\n\nMany factors contribute to whether a college is a good fit for you, such as campus culture, location, faculty, research opportunities, and extracurricular activities. If you\u2019re considering Tufts University, it would be beneficial to visit the campus, talk to current students or alumni, and review the specific engineering programs and faculty to determine if it aligns with your goals and interests.",
